# Implementation Plan: Firestore-Driven Blog CRUD

Migrating the current hardcoded blog system (in `BlogPage.tsx` and `BlogPostPage.tsx`) to a dynamic, real-time Firestore database with full CRUD capabilities in the admin dashboard.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Types & Data Layer

#### [NEW] [blog.ts](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/types/blog.ts)
- Define TypeScript interfaces for `BlogPost` and `BlogSection`.
- Properties:
  - `id`: string (slug for SEO-friendly URLs, e.g. `systems-first-scaling` instead of numeric IDs)
  - `title`: string
  - `subtitle`: string
  - `category`: string (can share categories with resources or define independent ones)
  - `date`: string (formatted creation date, e.g. "Sep 19, 2026")
  - `author`: string
  - `authorRole`: string
  - `readTime`: string (auto-calculated from word count)
  - `coverBg`: string (gradient fallback)
  - `coverLabel`: string (card display label)
  - `introduction`: string
  - `sections`: `BlogSection[]` (each section has a `heading`, `anchor`, and array of `paragraphs` or text)
  - `keyTakeaway`: string
  - `createdAt`, `updatedAt`: Firestore timestamps or ISO strings

#### [NEW] [blog.ts](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/lib/firestore/blog.ts)
- Implement CRUD operations for the `posts` Firestore collection:
  - `subscribeToPosts(callback)`: Real-time listeners.
  - `addPost(slug: string, data: Omit<BlogPost, 'id'>)`: Create new post.
  - `updatePost(id: string, data: Partial<BlogPost>)`: Update existing post.
  - `deletePost(id: string)`: Delete post.
  - `seedDefaultPosts()`: Wipe all posts and seed the 9 original hardcoded posts from the current blog files into Firestore.

#### [NEW] [useBlog.ts](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/hooks/useBlog.ts)
- Real-time React hook `useBlog()` that returns:
  - `posts`: Array of all blog posts
  - `loading`: boolean
  - `error`: Error | null

---

### 2. Admin Interface

#### [NEW] [AdminBlogPage.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/pages/admin/AdminBlogPage.tsx)
- Renders a table of all posts with columns: Title, Category, Author, Date, and Actions.
- Search input to filter posts by title/author.
- "Add Post" button opening the form modal.
- "Edit" and "Delete" button controls.
- "Reset & Seed Blog" button in Settings or here to restore the original articles.

#### [NEW] [BlogForm.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/components/admin/BlogForm.tsx)
- Form modal to handle adding/editing a blog post.
- Fields:
  - Title, Subtitle, Author, AuthorRole, Category (drawn dynamically from `useMetadata`), Cover BG (with gradient picker), Cover Label, Key Takeaway.
  - Introduction (textarea).
  - Dynamic Sections builder: allow users to add multiple sections. Each section has a Heading and a Content textarea. (Paragraphs are automatically split on double newlines `\n\n` on save).
  - URL Slug (generated from Title with override capability).
- Auto-calculates `readTime` based on total words in introduction + sections.

#### [MODIFY] [AdminSidebar.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/components/admin/AdminSidebar.tsx)
- Add "Blog Posts" tab in the admin navigation with a book icon.

#### [MODIFY] [AdminDashboardPage.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/pages/admin/AdminDashboardPage.tsx)
- Add a stats card showing the total count of blog posts.

#### [MODIFY] [AdminSettingsPage.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/pages/admin/AdminSettingsPage.tsx)
- Integrate a "Reset & Seed Blog Posts" button under the seed section.

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/App.tsx)
- Register route `/admin/blog` pointing to `AdminBlogPage`.

---

### 3. Public Pages Refactoring

#### [MODIFY] [BlogPage.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/pages/BlogPage.tsx)
- Replace local state arrays with data fetched from `useBlog()`.
- Sort by date or creation time.
- Update filters and search queries to run against Firestore data.

#### [MODIFY] [BlogPostPage.tsx](file:///home/frank/Documents/digitalife/src/pages/BlogPostPage.tsx)
- Retrieve current post by string slug (using `:id` parameter from react-router).
- Subscribe/fetch single post from the post list.
- Fallback safely to loading/not-found states.

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Type checking: `npx tsc --noEmit`
- Build test: `pnpm build`

### Manual Verification
1. Login to admin panel, navigate to settings, and click "Reset & Seed Blog Posts".
2. Go to the new "Blog Posts" tab, click "Add Post", write a new test post with sections, and save it.
3. Edit the post and confirm changes persist.
4. Go to the public Blog page, verify the new post is visible and category filtering works.
5. Click on the post to navigate to its SEO-friendly URL, verifying layout and content look premium.
6. Delete the post from the admin table and confirm it disappears from public view.
